____________________________________________________________________________________________________
WHAT:

This example shows classic Lagrange interpolation using dealII.
A function is defined at 'm' points . The function value is approximated at 'n' points, different 
from 'm' known points. 

The 'm' known points are called as sampling points and 
the 'n' unknown points are called as interpolation points.

Currently Gauss Lagrange points are implemented. Lobatto and Chebichev points are next line line.

____________________________________________________________________________________________________
WHY:

This tutorial gives a clear idea about dealII functional spaces, polynomials, iterators and workflow.
Only a few important features of dealII used in this tutorial, thus better understanding and less 
confusion.
Basic c++ classes used. Great for beginners. 

____________________________________________________________________________________________________
OTHER RESOURCES:

1. DealII tutorial programs (https://www.dealii.org/8.4.0/doxygen/deal.II/Tutorial.html)
2. CFD codes given on Dr. Praveen Chandrashekar's website (http://cpraveen.github.io/codes.html)
3. Video lectures of Dr. Wolfgang Bangerth (http://www.math.colostate.edu/~bangerth/videos.html)

____________________________________________________________________________________________________
TO RUN:
____________________________________________________________________________________________________
No.       command	 	Action                    Effect 			       
____________________________________________________________________________________________________
1.                           install deal.ii              you get DealII !                            
2.    cmake .                press enter                  extract                                
3.    make 		     press enter                  compile 		               
4.    ./interpolation	     press enter                  run  			       
5.    make distclean         press enter                  clean the folder                          
